<body>
    <form action="/trivandrum" method="get">
    <p id="p1">Thiruvananthapuram</p>
         <hr style="border-color:black;position:relative;top: 70px;">
         <div id="i1">
            <img id="apimg" src="https://images.cnbctv18.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Thiruvananthapuram-1019x573.jpg?impolicy=website&width=617&height=264">
        </div>
        <br><br><br><br><br>
        <div id="i2">
            <h2><strong><center>INFORMATION</center></strong></h2>
            <hr style="width: 950px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p>The capital city of Kerala, Thiruvananthapuram or Trivandrum, is a haven for beach lovers. Welcoming tourists from all over the world, Thiruvananthapuram poses as a perfect blend of rural and urban life. <br>

                With exotic beaches, resorts, roadside bars and cafés, this city is bliss for solo or honeymoon trips. <br>
                
                Best time to visit Thiruvananthapuram: October to March <br>
                Ideal Vacation Duration: 3-4 days <br>
                Average Expense: ₹ 2,799 per adult per day <br>
                Places to Visit in Thiruvananthapuram: Kanakakkunu Palace, Sri Padmanabhaswamy Temple, Kovalam Beach, Arruvy Waterfalls, Anchuthengu Fort <br>
                Things to Do in Thiruvananthapuram: Relax on beaches, try out water sports, try delicious seafood, visit temples, explore the fort palace and lighthouses. <br>
                </p>
            
        </div>
        <div id="i3">
            <center><h2>WEATHER</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;">
            <div class="icon">
            <h1><%=temp%>°C</h1><img src="/day/default.png" alt="" srcset="" id="image">
            </div>
            <h1 class="climate"><%=climate%></h1>
                <h2>Humidity : <%=humidity%>%<br><br>Wind Speed : <%=windspeed%>kmph</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="i4">
            <center><h2>TRANSPORTATION</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p> <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=oOAYqE64W2MO&format=png" height="25px" width="25px" alt="">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Air-Trivandrum International Airport is situated here.
                <br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=d8MqKVWJkyqN&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp; By Train-Trivandrum Railway station is located here. <br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=f42OOoV1ACzO&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Road-It is connected to major cities with national highways.</p>
        </div>
    </form>
    <script>
        
        let image=document.getElementById("image");

        let climate=document.querySelector(".climate").textContent;
        if(climate=="Mist"){
            image.src="/day/Mist.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Patchy rain possible"){
            image.src="/day/Patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Moderate rain"){
            image.src="/day/Moderate.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light rain shower"){
            image.src="/day/patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Partly cloudy"){
            image.src="/day/default.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Cloudy"){
            image.src="/day/Cloudy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Overcast"){
            image.src="/day/Cloudy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Sunny"){
            image.src="/day/Sunny.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Clear"){
            image.src="/day/Sunny.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Thundery outbreaks possible"){
            image.src="/day/Thunderstorm.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Fog"){
            image.src="/day/Fog.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light rain"){
            image.src="/day/Patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Moderate or heavy rain shower"){
            image.src="/day/Heavy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light drizzle"){
            image.src="/day/Drizzle.png"
        }
    
</script>
